Remarks were given by Vice President Pence in the Rose Garden on May 2, 2019, to mark the National Day of Prayer. The Vice President emphasized the importance of prayer throughout American history and the belief in prayer held by the American people. He highlighted that President Trump has made prayer a regular practice in the White House, even opening every Cabinet meeting with prayer. Pence also mentioned recent attacks on people of faith, expressing condolences and condemning the attacks. He stated that President Trump is a champion and defender of faith and religious liberty. The Vice President announced that the President would be taking further steps to acknowledge the role of people of faith and faith-based organizations in the nation. Pence concluded by asking for prayers for America and expressing confidence that prayer can bring healing to the nation.